String firstName;
String LastName;
}
Emp employee =new Emp(“John”,”Doe”);
Gets the form in XML as:


emp.xml

<emp>
	<employee>
		<firstname>John</firstname>
		<lastname>John</lastname>
	</employee>
	<employee>
		<firstname>Lee</firstname>
		<lastname>Con</lastname>
	</employee>
</emp>

open in browser..


JSON:

JavaScript Simple Object Notation: Key value pairs for each object, keys are the attributes and their value is the Object value.
Class Emp{
String firstName;
String LastName;
}
Emp employee =new Emp(“John”,”Doe”);

The JSON format :

var emp = {Employee1 : 
 				{firstName : “John”, lastName : “Doe”},
                 Employee2 : 
 				{firstName : “Lee”, lastName : “Con”}
  		};



var Emp={
  	Eid:101,
 		Ename:”Abc”,
 		Esal:10001
}
var Emps=[
{ 	Eid:101,
 		Ename:”Abc”,
 		Esal:10001
},
{		Eid:101,
 		Ename:”Abc”,
 		Esal:10001
}]





abcdef.html / abcdef.txt

